quite a giant leap in terms of </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Committee </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">procedures.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">I think it goes back to the point that we were making at the beginning in terms of leaving it to gut feeling </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">when</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> assigning a procedure, and the switch between the affirmative and the negative can lead to mistakes.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:bold">Q7 </span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Mr Nuttall:</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> Turning to the Henry VIII powers, have you come across any examples where they have been used inappropriately while you have been doing this?</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">Dr Fox</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">: In terms of the Bills we have looked at, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">there was the Legislative and Regulatory Reform Act; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">the initial powers on the Bill were very, very wide</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">. You </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">then </span><span sty