The </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">problem of going back to some of these—not small-bore reforms, but in the grand scheme of things perhaps they are—is that you are going to get exactly the same answers</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">. If you come away with the same answer, you are going to get the same response, and I think the debate needs to be broadened and widened.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The issues with sifting are</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">:</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> the issue of duplication</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> the issue of putting </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">on </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">a sticking plaster</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">the issue of whether </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">the horse has bolted</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> and it is </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">too late</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">; t</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">he degree to which the Committee would be very, very reliant on </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Clerks </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">and outside experts</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">; </span><span style="font-family:'